 by reflecting different diachronic stages, offer a window on the origin of switch reference, clause chaining, topic markers, postpositions and double-headed relative clauses. The book is relevant for readers interested in the typological, historical and cultural linguistics of New Guinea but also for anthropologists and historians because the history and cultural practices of Greater Awyu speakers are a key part of the story of this language family.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aKombai languagexGrammar. 0aKorowai languagexGrammar. 0aPapuan languagesxGrammar. 4aAwyu. 4aIndonesien. 4aPapuasprachen. 4aSprachtypologie. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aGreater Awyu.  aLinguistic Typology.  aPapuan Languages.  aWest Papua.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCz978311065906108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Frontlist 2020z978311074316608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020 Englishz978311070476108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020z9783110704563oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97815015069180 cprintz978150151556940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150150695640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501506956423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501506956/original  a978-3-11-065